result.name: Sake Central

reviews.text:
I went here early in the afternoon. The store is amazing. There's so much sake and other Japanese alcohol like Shochu and Whisky inside. 

Matteo was very knowledgeable and helped me pick sake I wanted. He also let me try some of the opened bottle. 

This a great spot to go to for learning and buying sake.

Came across this sake establishment by chance. Highly recommended. They have an extensive range of sake for you to try. Staff are friendly and extremely knowledgeable. Do not be afraid to ask and they’ll glad offer you recommendations and volunteer information about the different sakes. A great place to appreciate sake by the glass and bottles! Definitely found a place to hang out every other week. Looking forward to trying their bar menu too which was sold out on my first visit. —- UPDATE: went for dinner. It was absolutely a glorious experience. I highly recommend the tasting menu and let the staff recommend you the pairing sake. It is not cheap but worth every dollar. The staff are all knowledgable and service is prompt even on a busy night. I’ll be back for sure!

Sake list is abysmal. Glasses poured from the bottle are stale . Service is uninspiring and unhelpful. Do your self a favour and buy a bottle from apita and drink it in a gutter, you will feel just as at home as in sake central, but at better value.
So much love and effort in this place. The team super sharp and knowledgable! Definitely the best specialist place I have been to !
Enjoyed the same flights. Bartenders were also very knowledgeable about the Sake they were serving.
